Now he's taken over as Historian
for The Library of Congress,

00:06:23.150 --> 00:06:28.100
and we wish you well in
this new position, John.

00:06:28.100 --> 00:06:32.300
Now it's my opportunity to invite
four of our students to read

00:06:32.300 --> 00:06:34.470
from their writings that are

00:06:34.470 --> 00:06:38.640
in our book before we make
the official presentation.

00:06:38.640 --> 00:06:42.330
The first one is Stormy
Montez [Assumed Spelling],

00:06:42.330 --> 00:06:45.800
this is an 8th grade
student from Coastal Bend,

00:06:45.800 --> 00:06:48.120
Texas, Fulton Middle School.

00:06:48.120 --> 00:06:50.510
Stormy?

00:06:50.510 --> 00:07:08.260
[ Applause ]

00:07:08.260 --> 00:07:09.810
&gt;&gt; Stormy Montez: I
started from my sleep.

00:07:09.810 --> 00:07:12.150
I could hear the roaring
boom in my father's voice,

00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:14.230
like a train crashing
down the tracks.

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:22.540
Yelling and hitting, the
screams so loud and vulgar.

00:07:22.540 --> 00:07:25.640
I can see him hitting my
mom over and over again.

00:07:25.640 --> 00:07:28.400
This wasn't the first
time, they often fought.

00:07:28.400 --> 00:07:30.200
This time was different,
my mom was hitting back.

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:32.590
My sister and I watched,
crying and scared.

00:07:32.590 --> 00:07:34.120
We didn't know what to do.

00:07:34.120 --> 00:07:37.680
When my mom and dad saw us we
were told to return to bed.

00:07:37.680 --> 00:07:40.170
In the morning my dad was gone.

00:07:40.170 --> 00:07:43.050
We ended up losing
everything and having to move

00:07:43.050 --> 00:07:45.410
because the money had
been spent on drugs.

00:07:45.410 --> 00:07:47.900
Sadly, I know my father
abused drugs and was abusive,

00:07:47.900 --> 00:07:53.180
yet someday I just
want to say I love you.

00:07:53.180 --> 00:07:54.980
I wish this was the end
to my miserable story,

00:07:54.980 --> 00:07:56.950
but surely things got worse.

00:07:56.950 --> 00:07:58.970
I was dreadfully bullied
starting around the third grade,

00:07:58.970 --> 00:08:04.190
but began to gain weight and I no
longer looked like the other kids.

00:08:04.190 --> 00:08:07.700
It made me a perfect target.

00:08:07.700 --> 00:08:12.430
I tried so hard to not
let words get me down.

00:08:12.430 --> 00:08:17.350
The fact is I felt worse, like
a burden to everyone around me.

00:08:17.350 --> 00:08:19.890
I wanted it to finally stop.

00:08:19.890 --> 00:08:22.580
I remembered the words
that my grandpa told me,

00:08:22.580 --> 00:08:25.050
looking in my eyes, be strong.

00:08:25.050 --> 00:08:28.500
It wasn't long after I
started to bully other kids.

00:08:28.500 --> 00:08:30.380
It was interesting how it happened.

00:08:30.380 --> 00:08:33.600
I was finally accepted
by the cool kids,

00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:35.150
even though I knew they
weren't my friends,

00:08:35.150 --> 00:08:37.110
they just enjoyed watching
me get in trouble.

00:08:37.110 --> 00:08:41.420
I felt horrible when I bullied
them because I know how it felt.

00:08:41.420 --> 00:08:44.120
I understand their
pain all too well.

00:08:44.120 --> 00:08:45.850
I had to break the circle.

00:08:45.850 --> 00:08:49.160
I needed to work on
myself and needed help.

00:08:49.160 --> 00:08:56.010
It was taking a lot of work,
but I am much stronger now.

00:08:56.010 --> 00:09:01.020
So why do we behave like this?

00:09:01.020 --> 00:09:03.370
Hurting others, ourselves
feel better,

00:09:03.370 --> 00:09:07.640
acting violently by
hitting and injuring?

00:09:07.640 --> 00:09:14.310
Honestly, there are
countless causes for violence.

00:09:14.310 --> 00:09:18.200
Most people do not want
to make poor choices,

00:09:18.200 --> 00:09:25.120 position:56%
but we learn from what has been
modeled, be it positive or negative.

00:09:25.120 --> 00:09:29.530
Behaviors from violent video games
or movies in order to reduce,

00:09:29.530 --> 00:09:31.750
to prevent acts of violence.

00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:37.810
We must work and help people
feel safe, cared and supported,

00:09:37.810 --> 00:09:43.170 position:56%
also helping and develop healthy
sense of self-esteem and self-worth.

00:09:43.170 --> 00:09:46.280
I could have become bitter

00:09:46.280 --> 00:09:48.930
about what I have been
through, but I'm not.

00:09:48.930 --> 00:09:50.620
Instead I've learned to forgive

00:09:50.620 --> 00:09:55.330
and I will not be held
hostage by my past.

00:09:55.330 --> 00:09:56.630
My slate is clean.

00:09:56.630 --> 00:09:59.960
These obstacles have been painful.

00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:03.430
Today can show and
use these experiences

00:10:03.430 --> 00:10:07.690
to help the next generation
from being harassed and bullied.

00:10:07.690 --> 00:10:12.330
Though there may be one
person helping other youth

00:10:12.330 --> 00:10:15.390
to see their value, I
personally challenge each of you

00:10:15.390 --> 00:10:19.510
to break the cycle and help
influence someone for the better.

00:10:19.510 --> 00:10:37.580
[ Applause ]

00:10:37.580 --> 00:10:41.240
&gt;&gt; Dan Callister: We'd like to
now hear from Brenda Flores.

00:10:41.240 --> 00:10:43.400
Brenda is an 8th grader

00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:48.510
in Brightwood Education
Campus in Washington, D.C.

00:10:48.510 --> 00:10:57.900
[ Applause ]

00:10:57.900 --> 00:11:01.610
&gt;&gt; Brenda Flores: Violence
is a word with a big meaning.

00:11:01.610 --> 00:11:05.760 position:56%
Most of the people in this world use
violence to resolve their problems.

00:11:05.760 --> 00:11:09.360
When I think of the word violence
the first thing that comes

00:11:09.360 --> 00:11:14.350
to my mind is conflict, death,
war, a lot of negative things.

00:11:14.350 --> 00:11:18.960
In my opinion it's not necessary to
use violence to resolve a problem.

00:11:18.960 --> 00:11:21.900
You can talk and find a
way to solve your problem

00:11:21.900 --> 00:11:24.480
without hurting or killing someone.

00:11:24.480 --> 00:11:27.230
Violence has affected my
life because I used to live

00:11:27.230 --> 00:11:29.210
in El Salvador, now classified

00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:32.350
as the most dangerous
country in the whole world.

00:11:32.350 --> 00:11:35.550 position:56%
I couldn't go to school because I
was scared I'd get killed on my way.

00:11:35.550 --> 00:11:37.790
I couldn't play outside
because my mom was scared

00:11:37.790 --> 00:11:39.940
that I could get kidnapped.

00:11:39.940 --> 00:11:43.360
However, violence has
changed my life in a good way.

00:11:43.360 --> 00:11:48.230 position:56%
El Salvador was too dangerous, I had
to immigrate to the United States.

00:11:48.230 --> 00:11:50.380
The first day that I got
here I thought it was going

00:11:50.380 --> 00:11:55.310
to be really hard on me because
I didn't speak English and I knew

00:11:55.310 --> 00:11:57.920 position:56%
that everything was going to change.

00:11:57.920 --> 00:12:00.790
But now that I know the language
I have more opportunities

00:12:00.790 --> 00:12:02.090
than in El Salvador.

00:12:02.090 --> 00:12:05.410
Because of the violence most of our
parents would be working all day

00:12:05.410 --> 00:12:09.740
to give us what we need, but they
don't give us enough time to talk

00:12:09.740 --> 00:12:11.360
to them and say what we feel,

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:15.020
what type of friends we
have, who is around us.

00:12:15.020 --> 00:12:19.290
From the age 13 to 19 it's
important to get orientation

00:12:19.290 --> 00:12:24.830 position:56%
because at this age we are changing,
we're trying to find who we are.

00:12:24.830 --> 00:12:28.230
We should know that if
a person does drugs,

00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.850
isn't a good person
to be around with us.

00:12:30.850 --> 00:12:33.510
We can't be friends with
someone that is part of a gang

00:12:33.510 --> 00:12:34.810
because at some point they're going

00:12:34.810 --> 00:12:37.220
to tell you you should
join the gang.

00:12:37.220 --> 00:12:41.140
If you do this you are going to
get money, you're going to be cool,

00:12:41.140 --> 00:12:42.910
everyone is going to respect you.

00:12:42.910 --> 00:12:46.080
But we don't think that at the
end you're earning problems.

00:12:46.080 --> 00:12:49.370
What I can do to reduce youth
violence is try to help.

00:12:49.370 --> 00:12:53.430
What I mean with this is if I
know someone that is doing drugs

00:12:53.430 --> 00:12:57.270
or is part of a gang or is
thinking to join these things,

00:12:57.270 --> 00:13:01.480
to think really good what they
are going to do or they are doing.

00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:05.030
Because doing these things
is like a cycle that goes

00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:08.310
over and over and never ends.

00:13:08.310 --> 00:13:10.030
And tell them the consequences.

00:13:10.030 --> 00:13:13.420
If you do drugs you're going
to feel good at the beginning,

00:13:13.420 --> 00:13:16.870
but a few months later you're
going to get addicted to this.

00:13:16.870 --> 00:13:20.020
And if you don't have money
you're going to start stealing

00:13:20.020 --> 00:13:21.870
so you can get money
to buy the drugs.

00:13:21.870 --> 00:13:25.090
And at the end it's going
to end up killing you.

00:13:25.090 --> 00:13:27.150 position:56%
And if you're part of a gang, think,

00:13:27.150 --> 00:13:29.120
your family is going
to be in danger.

00:13:29.120 --> 00:13:32.460
Why? Because if you don't obey
them they already know everything

00:13:32.460 --> 00:13:36.440
about you, and if you run away
your family is going to pay for it.

00:13:36.440 --> 00:13:41.800
My advice is that don't let
people influence you or do things

00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:48.540
that you don't want to do
because at the end the one

00:13:48.540 --> 00:13:53.510
that is getting more hurt is you.

00:13:53.510 --> 00:13:56.180
So if you're doing
drugs ask for help,

00:13:56.180 --> 00:13:59.600
and if you're in a gang think what
are you doing, and if you feel

00:13:59.600 --> 00:14:02.980
like you need to talk to someone
talk with your parents or someone

00:14:02.980 --> 00:14:05.050
that is going to tell you
the right thing to do.

00:14:05.050 --> 00:14:08.520
Because if you keep doing
this at the end you're going

00:14:08.520 --> 00:14:10.920
to get more hurt than what
you're doing right now.

00:14:10.920 --> 00:14:12.440
And the consequences are worse

00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:15.510
because in this world what
you do is what you get.

00:14:15.510 --> 00:14:28.340
[ Applause ]

